value.value: Aurora kinase A (403 aa, ~46 kDa) is encoded by the human AURKA gene. This protein is involved in mediating microtubular structure and facilitating chromosome segregation during mitosis and meiosis.
Eukaryotic translation initiation factor 1 (113 aa, ~13 kDa) is encoded by the human EIF1 gene. This protein plays a role in scanning for and selection of a translation initiation site.
A form of dermatitis characterized by red, itchy, scaly, or crusty patches that can be chronic or intermittent.

One of the fifty states which is a member of the federation known as the United States of America. Other US geographic areas, such as Puerto Rico and the District of Columbia, are essentially equivalent to State when used in an address.
Actin, gamma-enteric smooth muscle (376 aa, ~42 kDa) is encoded by the human ACTG2 gene. This protein plays a role in the cytoskelton and cell motility.
Cell Mobility consists of passive translocation of the whole cell, or cell body, from one site to another.
Collagen alpha-1(I) chain (1464 aa, ~139 kDa) is encoded by the human COL1A1 gene. This protein is involved in the formation of fibrillar collagen.

A chromatographic technique in which the stationary phase is solid while the mobile phase is gaseous samples. The gaseous samples are separated based on their different adsorption ability to the solid phase.

Collagen alpha-2(I) chain (1366 aa, ~129 kDa) is encoded by the human COL1A2 gene. This protein is involved in the structural integrity of tendons, ligaments and bones through the formation of type I collagen fibrils.

Deoxyhypusine synthase (369 aa, ~41 kDa) is encoded by the human DHPS gene. This protein plays a role in the synthesis of deoxyhypusine and the post-translational modification of the eukaryotic translation initiation factor 5A-1 protein.

Amino Acid Biosynthesis consists of cellular enzymatic reactions that produce amino acids, organic compounds containing an amino and a carboxyl group and often used in protein synthesis by the formation of peptide bonds during ribosomal translation of mRNA. Several important amino acids, such as the neurotransmitter g-aminobutyric acid, have other functions than protein synthesis.
Accumulation of an excessive amount of fluid in cells or intercellular tissues.

Eukaryotic translation initiation factor 4E type 2 (245 aa, ~28 kDa) is encoded by the human EIF4E2 gene. This protein is involved in recognition of and binding to the 7-methylguanosine-containing mRNA cap during translation initiation.

A Translation Process consists of enzymatic reactions by which polypeptides are synthesized on ribosomes from information in mRNA transcripts to specify the sequence of amino acids in the polypeptide chain.

Translation Initiation consists of cellular and enzymatic reactions that instigate the process by which polypeptides are synthesized on ribosomes from information in mRNA transcripts to specify the sequence of amino acids in the polypeptide chain.

label.value: HLA Class II Histocompatibility Antigen, DP(W4) Beta Chain

value.value: HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DP(W4) beta chain (258 aa, ~29 kDa) is encoded by the human HLA-DPB1 gene. This protein plays a role in antigen presentation.
Heterogeneous nuclear ribonucleoprotein A/B (332 aa, ~36 kDa) is encoded by the human HNRNPAB gene. This protein plays a role in mRNA binding.

label.value: Mediator of RNA Polymerase II Transcription Subunit 24

value.value: Mediator of RNA polymerase II transcription subunit 24 (989 aa, ~110 kDa) is encoded by the human MED24 gene. This protein plays a role in transcriptional regulation.
Transforming acidic coiled-coil-containing protein 3 (838 aa, ~90 kDa) is encoded by the human TACC3 gene. This protein may play a role in centrosomal function.
A collection of fluid in a body cavity, which may be the result of a non-neoplastic disorder (e.g. heart failure) or a tumor (e.g. carcinoma of the lung).
A peripheral blood finding in which a large number of erythrocytes are shaped in an elliptical form.

label.value: Mouse Benign Sex Cord Stromal Mixed Tumor

value.value: A tumor embolism involves sudden blockage of an artery by a clot or by other material from tumor fragments transported by the blood stream.
